  m_text: "Fun Facts about Solar Systems\n\u25CF The Sun accounts for 99.86% of all
    the mass in the Solar System.\n\u25CF Light takes 8 minutes to travel from the
    Sun to Earth.\n(Pluto's distance).\n\u25CF Jupiter's Great Red Spot is a storm
    that has been raging for at least 350 years.\n\u25CF Saturn's rings are made
    of ice and rock, and are only about 10\u2013100 metres thick despite being 280,000
    km wide.\n\u25CF A day on Venus is longer than a year on Venus.\n"
