      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Our Solar System consists of the Sun and everything gravitationally bound
    to it: 8 planets, 5 dwarf planets, 293\nknown moons, and countless asteroids,
    comets, and dust particles. It formed approximately 4.6 billion years ago\nfrom
    a collapsing cloud of gas and dust. The Solar System extends from the Sun to
    the Oort Cloud \u2014 a vast sphere\nof icy bodies stretching up to 100,000 AU
    from the Sun, marking the boundary where the Sun's gravity barely\ndominates
    over the rest of the galaxy."
